data.text:
2023-24: Skated in all 32 games as a junior defender and finished the season with a goal and 10 assists for 11 points … Picked up an assist in Brown’s season-opening win over Holy Cross (Oct. 13) … Recorded two assists at Yale (Dec. 3) and one assist at New Hampshire (Dec. 10) … Added an assist against Quinnipiac (Jan. 27) and two helpers in the next game at Union (Feb. 2) … Recorded a goal in the second quarterfinal game against Colgate (Mar. 2).

2022-23: Named to the ECAC All-Academic Team ... Honorable Mention All-Ivy League ... Appeared in all 29 games for the Bears on defense ... Finished the year with three goals and six assists for nine points ... Scored goals at Harvard (Oct. 29), at Princeton (Jan. 21) and at Cornell (Feb. 10) ... Assisted on goals at Stonehill (Oct. 22), twice against Princeton (Nov. 4), against Cornell (Dec. 3), at Princeton (Jan. 21) and against St. Lawrence (Jan. 28).

2021-22: Named to the ECAC All-Academic Team...Named the team's Tara Mounsey Award winner as Best Defensive Player...Appeared in 26 games…Scored one goal and tied for fourth on the team with seven assists…Served as a top line defenseman…Led the Bears in plus/minus…Assisted on both of Brown’s goals in the season-opening 2-2 tie against Penn State…Added two more assists in a tie against Cornell on Nov. 6…Scored the game-winner in a 4-1 upset over No. 7 Yale on Jan. 28.

Before Brown: Competed in hockey and rugby at the Bill Crothers Secondary School … Also played for Etobicoke Junior Dolphins (2020-21), Toronto Junior Aeros (2019-20), Toronto Aeros Midget AA (2018-19), North York Storm Bantam AA (2017-18), Aurora Barbarians Rugby Club (2017-20) and the Ontario Junior Blues (2018-19) ... International Aurora Silver Stick Champion (2018), Kitchener-Waterloo USA Canada Cup Champion (2018), Best in the Nest Oakville Hornets Tournament Champion (2018), Toronto Aeros Holiday Classic Tournament Champion (2020) and Eastern National Rugby Champion with Team Ontario (2018 and 2019) ... Received the Bronze Medal at the Ontario Summer Games (2018) ... Selected to Hockey Canada's U18 Team Canada Summer Training Camp (2020) ... In rugby, helped her team win the Canlan YRAA Tier 2 Rugby 7's Championship (2018) ... Received the Aurora Barbarian Rugby Club Coaches Award (2018) ... U17 Ontario Rugby Club Champion (2019) ... Named Ontario Scholar in 2021 ... Achieved the Honour Roll (2017-21) ... Had the Highest Overall Female Average (2017-20) ... Received the Outstanding Achievement Award in Principles of Mathematics (2018 and 2019).

Personal: Daughter of Michele and Blaine Sikich ... Has two siblings, Scott and Eric ... Concentrating in Applied Math-Computer Science.
